{{Infobox journal | title = Atmospheric Environment | cover = | former_name = Atmospheric Environment, Part A: General Topics; Atmospheric Environment, Part B: Urban Atmosphere | abbreviation = Atmospheric Environ. | discipline = [[Atmospheric science]], [[environmental science]] | editor = C.K. Chan, H.B. Singh, A. Wiedensohler | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | history = 1967-present | frequency = 18/year | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.629 | impact-year = 2016 | ISSN = 1352-2310 | ISSN2 = 0960-1686 | ISSN2label = ''Atmospheric Environment, Part A: General Topics'': | ISSN3 = 0957-1272 | ISSN3label = ''Atmospheric Environment, Part B: Urban Atmosphere'': | ISSN4 = 0004-6981 | ISSN4label = ''Atmospheric Environment'' (1967-1989): | eISSN = | CODEN = AENVEQ | JSTOR = | LCCN = 94661961 | OCLC = 610395849 | website = http://www.journals.elsevier.com/atmospheric-environment/ | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/13522310 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/09601686 | link2-name = Online archive ''Atmospheric Environment, Part A: General Topics'' | link3 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/09571272 | link3-name = Online archive ''Atmospheric Environment, Part B: Urban Atmosphere'' | link4 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/00046981 | link4-name = Online archive ''Atmospheric Environment'' (1967-1989) }} '''''Atmospheric Environment''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering research pertaining to [[air pollution]] and other ways humans and natural forces affect the [[Earth's atmosphere]]. It was established in 1967. In 1990 it was split into two parts, ''Atmospheric Environment, Part A: General Topics'' and ''Atmospheric Environment, Part B: Urban Atmosphere'', which were merged again in 1994. The [[editors-in-chief]] are C.K. Chan ([[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]]), H.B. Singh ([[NASA Ames Research Center]]), and A. Wiedensohler ([[Leibniz Institute for Tropospheric Research]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2013 [[impact factor]] of 3.062.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Atmospheric Environment |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
